OL,3,CYoung girls in the UK drinking,
OL,4,Csmoking and vaping more than boys
OL,6,FThe UK seems to have more of an issue
OL,7,Fwith under-age vaping than many other
OL,8,Fcountries, with girls in the UK more
OL,9,Flikely to have used a vape by the age
OL,10,Fof 15 than the average for all 44
OL,11,Fcountries in the study. Vaping has
OL,12,Fovertaken smoking.
OL,14,FIn terms of alcohol consumption,
OL,15,Fchildren aged 11 and 13 in England are
OL,16,Fthe most likely to have ever drunk
OL,17,Falcohol compared with youngsters in
OL,18,Fall the other countries surveyed.
