OL,4,Csmoking and vaping more than boys
OL,6,FHe added: "Considering that the brain
OL,7,Fcontinues to develop well into a
OL,8,Fperson's mid-20s, adolescents need to
OL,9,Fbe protected from the effects of toxic
OL,10,Fand dangerous products.
OL,12,F"Unfortunately, children today are
OL,13,Fconstantly exposed to targeted online
OL,14,Fmarketing of harmful products, while
OL,15,Fpopular culture, like video games,
OL,16,Fnormalises them."
